accused%20had%20been%20acquitted%20twice%2C%20by%20two%20different%20benches%20of%20the%20high%20court.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20judges%20told%20Additional%20Solicitor%20General%20S.V.%20Raju%2C%20appearing%20for%20Maharashtra%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThere%20are%20two%20orders%20of%20acquittal%20by%20two%20different%20benches.%C2%A0%3Ci%3EPrima%20facie%3C%2Fi%3E%2C%20we%20find%20that%20the%20judgment%20is%20very%20well-reasoned.%20Since%20on%20an%20earlier%20occasion%2C%20this%20court%20had%20interfered%2C%20we%E2%80%99ll%20have%20to%20honour%20that.%20Otherwise%2C%20this%20is%20a%20very%20well-reasoned%20judgment%20by%20the%20high%20court.%20In%20ordinary%20course%2C%20we%20would%20not%20have%20entertained%20this%20appeal.%20The%20parameters%20of%20interference%20with%20acquittal%20orders%20are%20very%20limited.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIt%E2%80%99s%20a%20hard-earned%20acquittal.%20How%20many%20years%20has%20the%20man%20spent%20in%20jail%3F%E2%80%9D%20Justice%20Mehta%20added%2C%20followed%20by%20Justice%20Gavai%20saying%2C%20%E2%80%9CThe%20law%20is%20that%20there%20is%20a%20presumption%20of%20innocence.%20Once%20there%E2%80%99s%20an%20order%20of%20acquittal%2C%20that%20presumption%20gets%20fortified.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fsaibaba-acquittal-from-lack-of-sanction-to-dodgy-evidence-high-court-judgment-tears-into-states-case%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%20has%20reported%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20Bombay%20high%20court%20judgment%20had%20criticised%20both%20the%20state%E2%80%99s%20probe%20and%20the%20trial%20court%20judgment%20finding%20the%20men%20guilty.%20Justice%20Vinay%20G.%20Joshi%20and%20Justice%20Valimiki%20S.%20Menezes%20on%20March%205%20acquitted%20Saibaba%2C%20along%20with%20journalist%20Prashant%20Rahi%2C%20Mahesh%20Tikri%2C%20Hem%20Keshwdatta%20Mishra%20and%20Vijay%20Nan%20Tikri%20of%20all%20charges.%20The%20sixth%20person%20in%20the%20case%2C%20Pandu%20Narote%2C%20died%20in%20August%202022%2C%20awaiting%20this%20verdict.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESaibaba%2C%20who%20is%20wheelchair-bound%20and%20is%20over%2090%25%20handicapped%2C%20said%20he%20can%E2%80%99t%20move%20an%20inch%20without%20others%E2%80%99%20help.%20He%20said%20after%20his%20release%20that%20it%20is%20%E2%80%9C%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fit-is-only-by-chance-that-i-came-out-of-prison-alive-g-n-saibaba%5C%22%3Eonly%20by%20chance%3C%2Fa%3E%E2%80%9D%20that%20he%20is%20coming%20out%20of%20jail%20alive.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20the%20second%20time%20in%20two%20years%20that%20the%20Nagpur%20bench%20has%20acquitted%20Saibaba%20and%20others.%20On%20October%2014%2C%202022%2C%20the%20same%20court%2C%20comprising%20of%20Justice%20Rohit%20B.%20Deo%20and%20Anil%20Pansare%20had%20overturned%20the%20Gadchiroli%20session%20court%E2%80%99s%20judgement.%20Barring%20Vijay%20Tikri%2C%20who%20was%20convicted%20to%20ten%20years%20rigorous%20punishment%2C%20the%20others%20were%20awarded%20life%20sentences.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202022%2C%20discharging%20all%20five%20accused%2C%20Justice%20Deo%20had%20observed%20that%20the%20due%20process%20of%20law%20cannot%20be%20sacrificed%20at%20the%20altar%20of%20%E2%80%9Cperceived%20peril%20to%20national%20security%E2%80%9D.%20The%20bench%20directed%20the%20convicts%20to%20be%20released%20forthwith%20from%20jail%20unless%20they%20are%20accused%20in%20any%20other%20case.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20defence%20lawyers%20appearing%20for%20Saibaba%20and%20others%20had%20challenged%20the%20validity%20of%20the%20sanction%20order%20issued%20to%20prosecute%20under%20the%20stringent%20provisions%20of%20the%20Unlawful%20Activities%20(Prevention)%20Act%20(UAPA).%20They%20had%20relied%20on%20Section%2041%20(A)%20of%20the%20UAPA%20which%20clearly%20states%20that%2C%20%E2%80%9CNo%20court%20shall%20take%20cognizance%20of%20any%20offence%20without%20the%20previous%20sanction%20of%20the%20Central%20Government%20or%20any%20officer%20authorised%20by%20the%20Central%20Government%20on%20this%20behalf%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20HC%20in%202022%20had%20called%20the%20absence%20of%20a%20valid%20sanction%20order%20as%20%E2%80%9Cbad%20in%20law%20and%20invalid%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEven%20with%20the%20HC%E2%80%99s%20order%2C%20the%20Nagpur%20central%20jail%20authorities%20had%20refused%20to%20release%20them%20immediately%20and%20meanwhile%2C%20the%20state%20government%20had%20rushed%20to%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20seeking%20stay%20on%20the%20order%2C%20and%20had%20received%20one.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1710151218000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F07181050%2Fimage-1914.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fvery-well-reasoned-sc-refuses-to-stay-bombay-hc-order-acquitting-saibaba-others%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%26quot%3BIt's%20a%20hard-earned%20acquittal.%20How%20many%20years%20has%20the%20man%20spent%20in%20jail%3F%26quot%3B%20Justice%20Mehta%20said.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fvery-well-reasoned-sc-refuses-to-stay-bombay-hc-order-acquitting-saibaba-others%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Mortgage%20Interest%20Rates%20Today%2C%20March%2011%2C%202024%20%7C%20Rates%20Are%20Down.%20But%20High%20Inflation%20Could%20Send%20Them%20Back%20Up.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EThe%20offers%20and%20details%20on%20this%20page%20may%20have%20updated%20or%20changed%20since%20the%20time%20of%20publication.%20See%20our%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbest-mortgage-refinance-rates-today-monday-11-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20current%20information.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOur%20experts%20answer%20readers'%20home-buying%20questions%20and%20write%20unbiased%20product%20reviews%20(%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.b