0higher%20than%20Rs%201%20crore%2C%20when%20VIPs%20or%20the%20PMO%20refers%20a%20case%2C%20when%20directions%20are%20received%20from%20a%20court%2C%20when%20senior%20citizens%20make%20requests%20or%20when%20a%20case%20involves%20genuine%20hardship.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftaxguru.in%2Fincome-tax%2Fguidelines-priority-turn-disposal-appeals-csit-au-csit-appeals.html%5C%22%3EPrevious%20guidelines%20issued%20in%20December%202021%3C%2Fa%3E%20also%20mentioned%20five%20situations%20but%20VIP%20or%20PMO%20references%20were%20not%20one%20of%20them.%20Instead%2C%20they%20contained%20a%20provision%20for%20expeditious%20disposal%20where%20refunds%20were%20higher%20than%20Rs%201%20lakh.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20new%20guidelines%2C%20issued%20on%20Thursday%20(March%207)%2C%20deal%20with%20appeals%20pending%20at%20the%20Commissioner%20of%20Income%20Tax%20(Appeal%2FAppeal%20Unit)%20and%20Additional%20or%20Joint%20Commissioner%20of%20Income%20Tax%20(Appeal)%20organisational%20levels.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThey%20say%20that%20requests%20for%20expeditious%20disposal%20that%20are%20either%20raised%20at%20the%20appellant%E2%80%99s%20instance%2C%20or%20are%20referred%20by%20an%20assessing%20officer%20or%20a%20range%20head%2C%20%E2%80%9Cmay%20be%20considered%E2%80%9D%20by%20Principal%20Commissioners%2C%20Chief%20Commissioners%20or%20Directors%20General%20of%20Income%20Tax%20on%20the%20basis%20of%20recommendations%20made%20by%20jurisdictional%20principal%20income%20tax%20commissioners%20among%20other%20ranks.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20far%20as%20appeals%20within%20the%20jurisdiction%20of%20faceless%20income%20tax%20appeals%20commissioners%20are%20concerned%2C%20the%20new%20guidelines%20say%20that%20requests%20for%20expeditious%20disposals%20shall%20be%20referred%20to%20a%20Principal%20Chief%20Commissioner%20of%20Income%20Tax%20(National%20Faceless%20Appeal%20Centre).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fnarendra-modi-launches-new-transparent-taxation-platform-faceless%5C%22%3E%E2%80%98faceless%E2%80%99%20income%20tax%20assessment%20and%20appeals%20system%3C%2Fa%3E%20was%20created%20in%202020%20so%20that%20taxpayers%20would%20not%20have%20to%20physically%20visit%20income%20tax%20offices%20or%20meet%20officials%20in%20person.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20was%20intended%20to%20increase%20convenience%20for%20taxpayers%20and%20rein%20in%20corruption.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1710150640000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2019%2F10%2F24135657%2Fcash-india.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fpmo-vip-references-expeditious-income-tax-appeal-disposal-cbdt%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20Central%20Board%20of%20Direct%20Taxes%20said%20this%20while%20issuing%20fresh%20and%20superseding%20guidelines%20last%20week%20on%20when%20senior%20officials%20can%20choose%20to%20expedite%20the%20disposal%20of%20income%20tax%20appeals.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fpmo-vip-references-expeditious-income-tax-appeal-disposal-cbdt%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22SC%20refuses%20to%20stay%20HC%20order%20transferring%20Sandeshkhali%20case%20to%20CBI%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1710150267000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-108392399%2Cimgsize-966095.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Findia%2Fsc-refuses-to-stay-calcutta-hc-order-transferring-sandeshkhali-ed-attack-case-to-cbi%2Farticleshow%2F108392394.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22TOI%20NEWS%20DESK%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Findia%2Fsc-refuses-to-stay-calcutta-hc-order-transferring-sandeshkhali-ed-attack-case-to-cbi%2Farticleshow%2F108392394.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Fed%20Chairman%20Jerome%20Powell%20could%20wind%20up%20deciding%20the%20presidential%20election%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Photo%20Collage%20featuring%20Jerome%20Powell%20holding%20a%20scale.%20On%20one%20side%20of%20the%20scale%20is%20a%20picture%20of%20Donald%20Trump%2C%20and%20on%20the%20opposite%20side%20is%20an%20image%20of%20President%20Biden%2C%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65eb7f22ce7f1785b2e827cc%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22600%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EChip%20Somodevilla%2FGetty%20Images%3B%20Matt%20Rourke%2FAP%3B%20Sarah%20Silbiger%2FBloomberg%20via%20Getty%20Images%3B%20Alyssa%20Powell%2FBI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpowell-60-minutes-interview-fed-interest-rate-cuts-before-election-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EJay%20Powell%3C%2Fa%3E%20would%20very%20much%20like%20to%20stay%20out%20of%20politics%2C%20especially%20in%20an%20election%20year.%20The%20Federal%20Reserve%20chair%20doesn't%20want%20to%20be%20perceived%20as%20having%20a%20horse%20in%20the%20race%20come%20November%2C%20especially%20when%20one%20of%20said%20horses%20%E2%80%94%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-interest-rate-cuts-powell-help-democrats-win-elections-inflation-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EDonald%20Trump%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20is%20definitely%20going%20to%20be%20attacking%20him%20from%20any%20angle%20he%20can.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPowell%2C%20who%20was%20appointed%20as%20Fed%20chair%20by%20Trump%20and%20then%20reappointed%20by%20Joe%20Biden%2C%20has%20gone%20to%20great%20lengths%20to%20emphasize%20that%20the%20central%20bank%20is%20above%20the%20political%20fray.%20He%20has%20repeatedly%20emphasized%20that%20he%20and%20the%20other%20members%20of%20the%20Federal%20Open%20Market%20Committee%20are%20focused%20solely%20on%20economic%20data%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20a%20decision%20on%20monetary%20policy%20%E2%80%94%20which%2C%20at%20the%20moment%2C%20is%20whether%20to%20cut%20interest%20rates.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20a%20hearing%20Wednesday%2C%20Rep.%20Patrick%20McHenry%2C%20the%20Republican%20from%20North%20Carolina%20who%20chairs%20the%20House%20Financial%20Services%20Committee%2C%20noted%20that%20some%20people%20were%20predicting%20that%20the%20Fed%20would%20cut%20interest%20rates%20multiple%20times%20this%20year%2C%20while%20others%20predicted%20it%20would%20do%20nothing.%20The%20divergence%20between%20the%20cuts%20and%20no-cuts%20camps%20has%20been%20the%20biggest%20economic%20argument%20of%20the%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhat%20say%20you%3F%26quot%3B%20McHenry%20asked%20Powell.%20The%20Fed%20chair's%20response%3A%20%26quot%3BI%20say%20that%2C%20really%2C%20it%20will%20depend%20on%20the%20economy.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBeyond%20the%20academic%20argument%2C%20whether%20the%20Fed%20cuts%20interest%20rates%20has%20a%20significant%20political%20bearing%20this%20year.%20The%20economy%20and%20perceptions%20of%20it%20will%20be%20vital%20factors%20in%20determining%20what%20voters%20do%20when%20they%20head%20to%20the%20ballot%20box%20in%20the%20fall.%20It's%20an%20economy%20that%20Powell%20very%20much%20has%20a%20hand%20in%20shaping.%20Because%20of%20that%2C%20he%20really%20is%20in%20the%20center%20of%20the%20storm.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BImplicitly%2C%20explicitly%2C%20passively%2C%20or%20actively%2C%20the%20Fed%20is%20making%20decisions%20that%20can%20have%20high-leverage%20influence%20over%20the%20economy%20and%20economic%20outcomes%2C%26quot%3B%20Skanda%20Amarnath%2C%20the%20executive%20director%20of%20the%20advocacy%20group%20Employ%20America%2C%20said.%20%26quot%3BThe%20Fed%20matters%20to%20the%20state%20of%20the%20economy%2C%20and%20the%20state%20of%20the%20economy%20isn't%20irrelevant%20to%20electoral%20outcomes.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20moment%2C%20the%20US%20economy%20is%20in%20pretty%20good%20shape.%20The%20labor%20market%20is%20robust%2C%20and%20growth%20is%20strong.%20Inflation%20is%20coming%20back%20down%2C%20though%20it's%20not%20yet%20at%20the%20Fed's%202%25%20target.%20A%20soft%20landing%20%E2%80%94%20meaning%20things%20settle%20back%20down%20to%20earth%20without%20a%20recession%20%E2%80%94%20is%20in%20view.%20Still%2C%20while%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fnews%2Fetf%2Fconsumer-sentiment-hits-31-month-high-in-february-inflation-expectations-edge-higher-1033076668%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Econsumer%20sentiment%20has%20improved%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20where%20it%20was%2C%20say%2C%20six%20months%20ago%2C%20it's%20not%20great.%20Inflation%20has%20cooled%2C%20but%20prices%20are%20still%20higher%20than%20they%20used%20to%20be.%20So%20are%20interest%20rates%2C%20which%20the%20Fed%20hiked%20to%20combat%20inflation.%20Voters%20are%20unhappy%20about%20higher%20prices%2C%20and%20they%20feel%20weighed%20down%20by%20high%20interest%20rates%2C%20too.%20A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nber.org%2Fpapers%2Fw32163%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erecent%20working%20paper%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20former%20Treasury%20Secretary%20Larry%20Summers%20and%20a%20group%20of%20economists%20found%20that%20high%20borrowing%20costs%20were%20a%20major%20driver%20weighing%20down%20people's%20moods.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BConsumers%2C%20unlike%20modern%20economists%2C%20consider%20the%20cost%20of%20money%20part%20of%20their%20cost%20of%20living%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20authors%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20tracks.%20Interest%20rates%20may%20seem%20abstract%2C%20but%20they%20can%20have%20a%20real%20impact%20on%20how%20people%20view%20their%20financial%20situations.%20If%20you're%20in%20the%20market%20for%20a%20house%20right%20now%2C%20mortgage%20rates%20are%20eye-popping%20compared%20with%20a%20few%20years%20ago.%20Maybe%20you%20waited%20for%20car%20prices%20to%20settle%2C%20only%20to%20discover%20now%20that%20you%20can't%20afford%20a%20loan.%20Or%20you%20run%20a%20small%20business%2C%20and%20suddenly%20the%20cost%20of%20borrowing%20keeps%20you%20up%20at%20night.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20White%20House%20can't%20go%20back%20in%20time%20and%20reverse%20the%20sudden%20rise%20in%20inflation%20%E2%80%94%20in%20which%20the%20Fed%2C%20by%20waiting%20too%20long%20to%20raise%20interest%20rates%2C%20had%20a%20hand.%20But%20lowering%20interest%20rates%20should%20make%20people%20feel%20better%20about%20economic%20conditions%20and%20could%20give%20Democrats%20and%20Biden%20a%20boost.%20While%20the%20Fed%20has%20projected%20that%20it%20will%20start%20cutting%20rates%20at%20some%20point%20this%20year%2C%20the%20timing%20is%20an%20open%20question.%20March%3F%20May%3F%20June%3F%20Later%3F%20The%20answer%20to%20that%20question%20could%20seriously%20influence%20the%20outcome%20in%20November.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BInterest%20rates%20are%20a%20big%20reason%20why%20people%20are%20frustrated%2C%20independent%20of%20inflation%2C%20independent%20of%20whatever%20other%20economic%20outcomes%20may%20be%20frustrating%2C%26quot%3B%20Amarnath%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI'm%20not%20saying%20anything%20new%20here%20%E2%80%94%20Trump%20says%20it%2C%20too.%20He's%20well%20aware%20lower%20interest%20rates%20would%20boost%20the%20economy%2C%20lift%20people's%20moods%2C%20and%2C%20ultimately%2C%20help%20the%20party%20in%20charge.%20It's%20why%20he%20publicly%20worried%20the%20Fed%20would%20lower%20interest%20rates%20to%20help%20Hillary%20Clinton's%20presidential%20bid%20ahead%20of%20the%202016%20election%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-considering-firing-jerome-powell-fed-chair-rate-hike-2018-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erepeatedly%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-attacks-federal-reserve-powell-over-economy-gm-rate-hikes-2018-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eberated%3C%2Fa%3E%20Powell%20and%20the%20Fed%20over%20interest-rate%20increases%20while%20he%20was%20in%20the%20White%20House.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Fed%20is%20an%20independent%20body%20designed%20to%20be%20outside%20politics%2C%20so%20it's%20not%20subject%20to%20short-term%20pressures%20as%20it%20tries%20to%20steward%20the%20economy.%20There%20have%20been%20moments%20in%20the%20past%20when%20presidents%20have%20tried%20to%20sway%20it%20%E2%80%94%20often%20with%20disastrous%20results.%20Richard%20Nixon%20pressured%20the%20Fed%20to%20keep%20interest%20rates%20low%20before%20his%20reelection%2C%20which%20helped%20cement%20the%20disastrous%20inflation%20of%20the%201970s.%20Ronald%20Reagan%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fronald-reagan-fed-chair-volcker-trump-2018-10%23%3A~%3Atext%3DAccording%2520to%2520Volcker%252C%2520Reagan%2520did%2Celection%252C%2522%2520Baker%2520told%2520Volcker.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Egot%20the%20message%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20the%20central%20bank%20on%20his%20wants%20during%20his%20presidency%2C%20getting%20his%20chief%20of%20staff%20to%20tell%20then-Fed%20Chair%20Paul%20Volcker%20not%20to%20raise%20rates%20ahead%20of%20his%20reelection%20campaign.%20Volcker%20wasn't%20planning%20to%20raise%20rates%20anyway.%20In%20recent%20decades%2C%20however%2C%20most%20presidents%20shied%20away%20from%20saying%20much%2C%20until%20Trump.%20Most%20observers%20take%20Powell%20at%20his%20word%20that%20the%20Fed%20is%20not%20going%20to%20take%20politics%20into%20account%20in%20interest-rate%20decisions%2C%20even%20in%20an%20election%20year.%20But%20that%20doesn't%20mean%20he%20exists%20in%20a%20bubble%2C%20either.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20don't%20think%20Powell%20is%20thinking%20about%20whether%20Trump%20or%20Biden%20will%20tell%20him%20to%20cut%20or%20hike%20rates%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Elizabeth%20Pancotti%2C%20the%20director%20of%20special%20initiatives%20at%20Roosevelt%20Forward%2C%20a%20sister%20organization%20of%20the%20progressive%20think%20tank%20the%20Roosevelt%20Institute.%20%26quot%3BIt%20might%20affect%20how%20he%20messages%20the%20rate%20hikes%20or%20cuts.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20in%20non-election%20years%2C%20Fed%20officials%20are%20incredibly%20cautious%20with%20their%20words.%20The%20political%20optics%20could%20make%20them%20even%20more%20so.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20take%20Powell%20at%20his%20word%20that%20they're%20not%20making%20policy%20with%20an%20eye%20to%20explicitly%20putting%20their%20finger%20on%20the%20scale%20for%20one%20party%20or%20one%20presidential%20candidate%20over%20the%20other%2C%20but%20the%20Fed%20certainly%20has%20to%20manage%20political%20risk%2C%26quot%3B%20Sarah%20Binder%2C%20a%20political%20scientist%20at%20George%20Washington%20University%2C%20said.%20Full%20FOMC-meeting%20transcripts%2C%20which%20are%20kept%20secret%20for%20five%20years%2C%20show%20the%20Fed%20isn't%20immune%20to%20political%20winds.%20Transcripts%20from%202018%2C%20for%20example%2C%20show%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bloomberg.com%2Fnews%2Farticles%2F2024-01-12%2Ffed-s-2018-transcripts-show-desire-to-shore-up-political-support%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eofficials%20discussed%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20need%20for%20political%20support%20for%20their%20decisions%20and%20were%20well%20aware%20of%20outside%20pressure.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20Fed%20doesn't%20really%20want%20to%20rock%20the%20boat.%20It%20doesn't%20want%20to%20upset%20Congress.%20It%20needs%20Congress%20on%20its%20side.%20They%20don't%20want%20Congress%20reopening%20the%20Federal%20Reserve%20Act%2C%26quot%3B%20Binder%20said.%20%26quot%3BThe%20Fed%20can't%20avoid%20the%20political%20winds%20here.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENot%20everything%20about%20the%20economy%20is%20under%20the%20Fed's%20control%2C%20of%20course%2C%20meaning%20there's%20only%20so%20much%20Powell%20can%20be%20blamed%20for%2C%20politically%20or%20otherwise.%20If%20the%20avian%20flu%20strikes%20again%20and%20chickens%20start%20to%20get%20sick%20en%20masse%2C%20egg%20prices%20are%20going%20to%20go%20back%20up.%20The%20central%20bank%20can't%20do%20much%20about%20oil%20and%20gas%20prices%2C%20which%20depend%20on%20global%20market%20forces%20or%20geopolitical%20turmoil.%20What's%20more%2C%20most%20Americans%20don't%20think%20about%20the%20Fed%20very%20much%20at%20all%20as%20a%20factor%20in%20their%20economic%20lives%2C%20even%20if%20it%20is%20one.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPowell%20is%20walking%20a%20tightrope%20right%20now%20in%20more%20ways%20than%20one.%20The%20economic%20risks%20of%20the%20Fed's%20decisions%20are%20real%20%E2%80%94%20if%20it%20cuts%20rates%20too%20soon%2C%20inflation%20could%20start%20to%20pick%20up%20again%2C%20and%20if%20it%20waits%20too%20long%2C%20it%20could%20put%20too%20much%20of%20a%20damper%20on%20the%20economy%20and%20push%20the%20country%20into%20a%20recession.%20It's%20a%20bit%20of%20a%20Goldilocks%20situation%2C%20except%20a%20lot%20more%20is%20at%20stake%20in%20finding%20what's%20just%20right%20than%20a%20good%20night's%20sleep.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey've%20got%20to%20do%20the%20best%20job%20they%20can.%20The%20ante%20for%20them%20internally%20is%20to%20do%20this%20just%20by%20the%20book%20as%20much%20as%20possible%20as%20an%20institution%2C%26quot%3B%20Diane%20Swonk%2C%20the%20chief%20economist%20at%20KPMG%20US%2C%20said.%20%26quot%3BThe%20Fed%20doesn't%20have%20a%20horse%20in%20this%20race%2C%20and%20it%20never%20does%2C%20but%20it%20will%20always%20be%20blamed.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Femily-stewart%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EEmily%20Stewart%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20is%20a%20senior%20correspondent%20at%20Business%20Insider%2C%20writing%20about%20business%20and%20the%20economy.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffederal-reserv