2C%20during%20an%20impromptu%20press%20conference%2C%20President%20Biden%20said%20his%20memory%20is%20%E2%80%9Cfine%E2%80%9D%20and%20lambasted%20a%20Justice%20Department%20report%20on%20his%20handling%20of%20classified%20information%2C%20particularly%20its%20questions%20about%20his%20mental%20acuity%20and%20age.%20Biden%20answered%20defiantly%20%E2%80%94%20and%20sometimes%20angrily%20%E2%80%94%20questions%20about%20his%20capacity%20to%20continue%20serving%20in%20the%20White%20House.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EYet%20even%20as%20he%20defended%20himself%20against%20a%20tide%20of%20scrutiny%20about%20his%20mental%20fitness%2C%20Biden%20mistakenly%20referred%20to%20Egyptian%20President%20Abdel%20Fattah%20El-Sisi%20as%20the%20leader%20of%20Mexico.%20Before%20that%20he%20mixed%20up%20Helmut%20Kohl%20and%20Angela%20Merkel%20of%20Germany%20and%20Mitterrand%20and%20Macron%20of%20France.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20a%20good%20week%20for%20Trump%20%E2%80%94%20the%20US%20Supreme%20Court%20overturned%20an%20attempt%20to%20block%20him%20from%20the%20ballot%20in%20Colorado%20and%20polls%20showed%20him%20ahead%20of%20Biden%20in%20the%20presidential%20race.%20On%20Super%20Tuesday%2C%20Trump%20secured%20victories%20in%20several%20Republican%20primaries%20across%20the%20country.%20His%20only%20major%20challenger%2C%20former%20South%20Carolina%20governor%20Nikki%20Haley%2C%20dropped%20out%20last%20week%20after%20his%20Super%20Tuesday%20triumph.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitical-economy%2Fdonald-trump-businesses-india-presidency%5C%22%3EIndia%205th%20Among%2020%20Countries%20that%20Gave%20Trump%20Businesses%20of%20%247.8M%20During%20Presidency%3A%20Report%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20former%20president%20has%20doubled%20down%20on%20the%20most%20controversial%20aspects%20of%20his%20first%20term%2C%20threatening%20to%20abandon%20NATO%20allies%20and%20promise%20to%20tackle%20illegal%20immigration.%20Domestically%2C%20abortion%20or%20what%20Biden%20chose%20to%20refer%20to%20as%20%E2%80%98reproductive%20freedom%20in%20his%20SOTU%20is%20a%20major%20issue%20in%20this%20election%20and%20both%20candidates%20hold%20contrasting%20opinions%20on%20it.%20With%20Trump%20leaning%20toward%20restricting%20abortion%2C%20the%20motivation%20to%20vote%20is%20significantly%20higher%20on%20the%20Democratic%20side%20now.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EDifference%20in%20perspective%20does%20not%20translate%20into%20fundamentally%20different%20positions%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECreating%20an%20unusual%20spectacle%2C%20Biden%20and%20Trump%20recently%20travelled%20to%20Texas%20border%20towns%2C%20acknowledging%20the%20centrality%20of%20the%20immigration%20issue.%20Opinion%20polls%20show%20broad%20public%20disapproval%20of%20how%20President%20Biden%20has%20handled%20the%20surge%20in%20illegal%20border%20crossings%2C%20averaging%202%20million%20per%20year%20since%202021.%20Although%20Trump%2C%20also%20faced%20criticism%20for%20his%20immigration%20policies%2C%20he%20is%20perceived%20as%20more%20effective%20against%20illegal%20immigration.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETheir%20foreign%20policy%20positions%20are%20harder%20to%20discern.%20Overtly%2C%20Trump%E2%80%99s%20presidency%20was%20rooted%20in%20unilateralism%2C%20confrontation%2C%20and%20a%20focus%20on%20%E2%80%9CAmerica%20First%2C%E2%80%9D%20Biden%20adopted%20the%20phrase%2C%20%E2%80%98America%20is%20Back%E2%80%99%20emphasising%20diplomacy%20and%20multilateralism.%20This%20perspective%20does%20not%20however%20translate%20into%20fundamentally%20different%20positions%2C%20merely%20approach%20to%20foreign%20policy%20issues.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBiden%20has%20spent%20years%20chairing%20the%20Senate%20Foreign%20Relations%20Committee%20and%20foreign%20policy%20is%20considered%20his%20point%20of%20expertise.%20He%20took%20a%20big%20political%20punch%20for%20the%20drawdown%20in%20Afghanistan%2C%20but%20made%20good%20on%20a%20promise%20to%20get%20the%20United%20States%20out%20of%20Afghanistan.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20has%20been%20very%20aggressive%20in%20his%20support%20of%20Ukraine%20and%20steadfast%20in%20his%20support%20of%20Israel%2C%20which%20may%20be%20potentially%20jeopardising%20relationships%20with%20people%20within%20his%20own%20party%20who%20support%20the%20Palestinians.%20His%20administration%20had%20to%20make%20public%20calls%20for%20an%20immediate%20ceasefire%20in%20Gaza.%20Trump%20has%20called%20Gaza%20militant%20group%20Hamas%20a%20%E2%80%9Cproblem%E2%80%9D%20stating%2C%20%E2%80%9CYou%E2%80%99ve%20got%20to%20finish%20the%20problem.%20You%20had%20a%20horrible%20invasion.%20It%20took%20place.%20It%20would%20have%20never%20happened%20if%20I%20was%20president%2C%20by%20the%20way.%E2%80%9D%20And%20so%20that%20can%20have%20electoral%20ramifications.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETrump%20who%20earlier%20withheld%20military%20aid%20to%20Ukraine%20impeachment%20proceedings%2C%20has%20now%20declared%20that%20Russian%20President%20Vladimir%20Putin%20can%20%E2%80%9Cdo%20whatever%20the%20hell%20he%20wants%E2%80%9D%20with%20respect%20to%20NATO%20allies.%20Biden%20on%20the%20other%20hand%20opened%20his%20SOTU%20rallying%20for%20American%20support%20for%20Ukraine.%C2%A0%E2%80%9CWe%20will%20not%20walk%20away.%20We%20will%20not%20bow%20down.%20I%20will%20not%20bow%20down.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENo%20change%20expected%20in%20Indo-US%20ties%20and%20US%E2%80%99s%20China%20policy%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20is%20bipartisan%20support%20for%20expansive%20engagement%20with%20India.%20Both%20Prime%20Ministers%20Narendra%20Modi%20and%20Manmohan%20Singh%20were%20invited%20by%20Democratic%20presidents%20for%20rare%20US%20state%20visits.%20Republican%20administrations%20have%20historically%20been%20more%20suited%20to%20Indian%20sensibilities%20especially%20as%20they%20take%20less%20interest%20in%20concerns%20about%20India%E2%80%99s%20democracy%2C%20human%20rights%20and%20press%20freedoms.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBoth%20the%20Democrats%20and%20Republicans%20have%20courted%20the%20fairly%20affluent%20and%20educated%20Indian%20American%20vote%20bloc%2C%20largely%20residing%20in%20potential%20swing%20states%20like%20Texas%2C%20Michigan%20and%20Pennsylvania.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESo%20while%20augmenting%20Indo-US%20ties%20is%20a%20given%20for%20both%20candidates%2C%20it%20is%20their%20posture%20vis-a-vis%20China%20that%20generates%20the%20most%20interest.%20At%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmoderndiplomacy.eu%2F2023%2F11%2F21%2Fthe-us-china-equation-is-essentially-prone-to-embroilment%2F%5C%22%3EBiden-Xi%20meeting%20on%20the%20sidelines%20of%20the%20APEC%20Leaders%20summit%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20US%20there%20was%20an%20attempt%20to%20restore%20a%20degree%20of%20affability%20to%20an%20extremely%20hostile%20and%20competitive%20relationship.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDespite%20disagreeing%20with%20Trump%E2%80%99s%20China%20policy%2C%20the%20Biden%20administration%20has%20maintained%20existing%20tariffs%20and%20imposed%20restrictions%20on%20sharing%20technology.%20It%20is%20unlikely%20that%20the%20course%20of%20US%E2%80%99s%20China%20policy%20will%20alter%20fundamentally%20post%20elections%20whosoever%20assumes%20office.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMost%20voters%20decide%20for%20whom%20they%20will%20vote%20relatively%20early%20in%20the%20campaign%20season%20and%20the%20polls%20show%20Trump%20is%20ahead%2C%20however%20narrowly%2C%20in%20enough%20states%20right%20now%20to%20win%20the%20electoral%20college%20and%20the%20presidency.%20In%20the%20meantime%2C%20the%20Biden%20versus%20Trump%20campaign%20is%20witnessing%20intense%20competition%2C%20fierce%20online%20activities%20and%20abusive%20debates%20on%20social%20networks.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cspan%3EVaishali%3C%2Fspan%3E%C2%A0Basu%20Sharma%20is%20a%20strategic%20and%20economic%20affairs%20analyst.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1710147585000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%