%20essay%20is%20based%20on%20a%20conversation%20with%20Theresa%20Sue%20Mubenga%2C%20a%20former%20tech%20manager%20and%20startup%20founder.%20The%20following%20has%20been%20edited%20for%20length%20and%20clarity.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI've%20spent%20over%2010%20years%20in%20the%20corporate%20world%20in%20the%20tech%20sector.%20In%20my%20fourth%20year%2C%20I%20became%20a%20manager%2C%20and%20that's%20when%20I%20was%20first%20introduced%20to%20a%20PIP.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI've%20had%20to%20put%20four%20employees%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fannual-review-eliminating-jack-dorsey-block-square-trend-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eperformance%20improvement%20plans%3C%2Fa%3E%20(PIPs)%2C%20and%20all%20of%20them%20ended%20in%20termination.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EI%20had%20to%20put%20an%20employee%20on%20a%20PIP%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20had%20an%20employee%20who%20started%20off%20great.%20During%20the%20interview%20process%2C%20she%20was%20a%20no-brainer%20for%20all%20of%20us%3B%20she%20passed%20all%20of%20the%20layers%20of%20interviews%20with%20flying%20colors.%20Once%20she%20started%20working%20with%20us%2C%20she%20was%20so%20personable%20and%20so%20kind.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20within%20a%20few%20months%2C%20something%20happened.%20I%20don't%20know%20if%20it%20was%20hard%20for%20her%20to%20keep%20up%20this%20persona%20or%20if%20she%20was%20struggling%20with%20something%20on%20the%20side%2C%20but%20she%20completely%20switched.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20became%20unkind%20and%20rude.%20She%20no%20longer%20had%20the%20traits%20that%20we%20really%20valued%20when%20hiring%20her.%20Her%20primary%20job%20was%20in%20customer%20service%2C%20and%20we%20always%20got%20complaints%20from%20customers%20about%20how%20they%20felt%20like%20she%20had%20a%20disrespectful%20and%20short%20tone.%20She%20never%20fully%20completed%20her%20tasks%2C%20came%20to%20work%20late%2C%20and%20called%20out%20of%20work%20regularly.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20had%20weekly%20meetings%20with%20her%20where%20I%20asked%2C%20%26quot%3BHey%2C%20is%20there%20something%20going%20on%3F%20Is%20there%20something%20we%20could%20do%20better%3F%26quot%3B%20I%20felt%20like%20I%20was%20trying%20to%20be%20her%20therapist.%20But%20she%20felt%20personally%20attacked%20every%20time%20anyone%20would%20try%20to%20address%20anything%20with%20her.%20She%20would%20ask%20things%20like%2C%20%26quot%3BWhy%20is%20it%20only%20me%20being%20focused%20on%3F%26quot%3B%20and%20place%20blame%20on%20other%20people.%20She%20was%20highly%20sensitive%20and%20couldn't%20take%20criticism.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20higher-ups%20decided%20that%20the%20PIP%20was%20the%20best%20way%20to%20go%20about%20her%20termination%20because%20there%20was%20a%20risk%20that%20if%20we%20fired%20her%2C%20she%20would%20come%20back%20and%20say%20that%20the%20company%20illegally%20terminated%20her.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDuring%20those%2030%20days%20of%20the%20PIP%2C%20her%20behavior%20changed.%20She%20didn't%20miss%20or%20call%20out%20from%20work.%20She%20came%20in%20on%20time%20and%20was%20more%20proactive%20in%20finishing%20her%20tasks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20survived%20the%20PIP.%20No%20one%20could%20believe%20that%20someone%20had%20actually%20made%20it%20through%20a%20PIP.%20We%20thought%20it%20might%20be%20an%20act%2C%20but%20we%20were%20optimistic.%20We%20were%20like%2C%20%26quot%3BOkay%2C%20great!%20This%20is%20good.%20Maybe%20she%20changed%20her%20ways.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EHer%20behavior%20reverted%20after%20the%20PIP%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20soon%20as%20the%20PIP%20ended%2C%20she%20reverted%20to%20her%20old%20ways.%20The%20Monday%20after%20her%20PIP%20ended%2C%20she%20came%20into%20the%20office%20and%20was%20back%20to%20her%20cold%2C%20short-tempered%20nature.%20She%20was%20distant%20from%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20team%20and%20would%20talk%20back%20and%20have%20a%20snarky%20attitude.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20don't%20think%20she%20thought%20she%20could%20be%20put%20on%20another%20PIP%20or%20terminated.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20met%20with%20the%20company%20management%20and%20we%20discussed%20what%20we%20thought%20about%20her%20behavior%20during%20the%20PIP%20and%20after%20the%20PIP.%20We%20all%20agreed%20that%20it%20didn't%20help%20her%20and%20that%20she%20was%20hindering%20the%20team%20because%20we%20needed%20to%20hyperfocus%20on%20her%20and%20her%20struggles.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20were%20enough%20grounds%20for%20termination%2C%20so%20we%20started%20documenting%20all%20of%20the%20times%20she%20was%20late%2C%20called%20out%2C%20and%20received%20customer%20complaints.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWithin%2030%20days%20of%20surviving%20the%20PIP%2C%20she%20was%20terminated.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EI%20now%20understand%20the%20protection%20measures%20PIPs%20offer%20companies%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20hate%20putting%20people%20on%20PIPs.%20I'm%20naturally%20an%20empathetic%20person%20because%20I%20care%20a%20lot%20about%20people%20%E2%80%94%20I've%20been%20that%20way%20throughout%20my%20entire%20career.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20now%20that%20I%20run%20my%20own%20company%20with%2022%20employees%2C%20I%20have%20a%20slightly%20different%20perspective%20and%20think%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpip-performance-improvement-plan-how-to-survive-career-development-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EPIPs%20are%20very%20necessary%3C%2Fa%3E%20because%20of%20the%20protection%20measures%20they%20offer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20set%20out%20in%20writing%20the%20employee's%20behavior%20and%20the%20fact%20that%20the%20company%20is%20giving%20the%20employee%20a%20fair%20opportunity%20to%20change%20it.%20This%20protects%20the%20company%20from%20anyone%20claiming%20that%20they%20were%20illegally%20terminated.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20two%20years%20since%20starting%20my%20own%20company%2C%20I've%20had%20to%20put%20one%20person%20on%20a%20PIP.%20It%20was%20very%20hard.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20haven't%20changed%3B%C2%A0I%20still%20believe%20that%20there's%20an%20underlying%20reason%20for%20everyone's%20behavior%20and%20want%20to%20make%20sure%20we%20check%20in%20on%20if%20there's%20something%20going%20on%20in%20their%20personal%20life.%20But%20I%20do%20know%20having%20this%20mindset%20can%20be%20bad%20for%20business%2C%20so%20I've%20become%20more%20direct%20with%20decision-making.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EPIPs%20could%20actually%20be%20beneficial%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20used%20correctly%2C%20PIPs%20could%20be%20beneficial%20to%20employees.%20But%20companies%20need%20to%20put%20more%20good%20managers%20in%20place%20that%20care%20for%20their%20employees.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20a%20lot%20more%20bad%20managers%20than%20good%20managers.%20Good%20managers%20care%20about%20their%20people.%20They're%20going%20to%20approach%20everything%20in%20an%20empathetic%2C%20caring%2C%20and%20understanding%20way.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20there%20are%20bad%20managers%20who%20are%20just%20there%20for%20the%20bottom%20line.%20Bad%20managers%20might%20just%20decide%20to%20put%20an%20employee%20on%20a%20PIP%20so%20that%20they%20can%20get%20rid%20of%20them%20and%20don't%20have%20to%20deal%20with%20their%20behavior.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20the%20PIP%20to%20work%20how%20it%20should%2C%20where%20it's%20fair%20to%20both%20the%20employer%20and%20employee%2C%20requires%20having%20good%20middle%20management%20that%20can%20actively%20work%20with%20an%20employee%20and%20be%20their%20voice%20of%20reason.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EOnce%20you've%20been%20put%20on%20a%20PIP%2C%20here's%20what%20you%20should%20do%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20PIP%20is%20really%20a%20no-return%20kind%20of%20thing.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-to-do-if-placed-on-pip-microsoft-vp-leave-asap-2023-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EPIPs%20are%20not%20survivable%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20because%20once%20someone%20gets%20a%20PIP%2C%20they%20often%20fee