20the%20Israeli%20consulate%20was%20Gopal%20Godse%2C%20seeking%20assistance%20in%20printing%20and%20disseminating%20his%20speech%20in%20defence%20of%20his%20brother%2C%20Nathuram%20Godse%2C%20who%20had%20killed%20Mahatma%20Gandhi.%20The%20request%20was%20denied.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBased%20on%20foreign%20ministry%20documents%20released%20to%20the%20national%20archives%20in%20last%20two%20years%2C%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.haaretz.com%2Fisrael-news%2F2024-03-08%2Fty-article-magazine%2F.premium%2Fthe-india-file-israels-warm-ties-with-the-indian-far-right-began-decades-before-modi%2F0000018e-19a9-d7d3-abce-79a999a10000%5C%22%3Ea%20detailed%20report%20by%20human%20rights%20and%C2%A0%20freedom%20of%20information%20activist%20Eitay%20Mack%2C%20published%20by%20the%20Israeli%20newspaper%20%3Cem%3EHaaretz%2C%3C%2Fem%3E%20chronicles%3C%2Fa%3E%20Israel%E2%80%99s%20relationship%20with%20the%20far%20right%20in%20India%2C%20particularly%20the%20BJP%20and%20its%20predecessor%20Jan%20Sangh.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20diplomatic%20telegrams%20show%20that%20while%20Israeli%20diplomats%20explicitly%20referred%20to%20the%20far-right%20members%20as%20%E2%80%9Cfascist%E2%80%9D%20and%20noted%20that%20the%20ideology%20was%20based%20on%20a%20hatred%20of%20Muslims%2C%20the%20relations%20with%20the%20far%20right%20were%20carefully%20maintained.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia%20had%20recognised%20Israel%20on%20September%2017%2C%201950%2C%20but%20full-scale%20diplomatic%20ties%2C%20with%20the%20opening%20of%20embassies%20in%20capitals%2C%20only%20took%20place%20in%201992.%20During%20those%2040-0dd%20years%2C%20Israel%20was%20represented%20in%20India%20with%20a%20consulate%20in%20Mumbai.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Cem%3EHaaretz%3C%2Fem%3E%20report%20cites%20telegrams%20dating%20back%20to%20June%201965%2C%20when%20then-consul%20in%20Bombay%2C%20Peretz%20Gordon%2C%20wrote%20back%20to%20the%20Israeli%20foreign%20ministry%20that%20%E2%80%9Cto%20this%20day%20and%20in%20the%20future%2C%20the%20Hindu%20fears%20and%20hates%20the%20Muslim%20the%20same%E2%80%9D.%20He%20further%20claimed%20that%20the%20opposition%20BJP%20and%20in%20the%20right-wing%20circles%20of%20the%20Indian%20National%20Congress%2C%20%E2%80%9Cthis%20finds%20expression%20in%20various%20forms%20and%20even%20openly%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELess%20than%20a%20year%20later%2C%20Gordon%20wrote%20on%20April%2026%2C%201966%20about%20recommendations%20for%20strengthening%20ties%20with%20India%2C%20which%20included%20%E2%80%9Csecret%20communications%20with%20oppositional%20elements%20for%20the%20purpose%20of%20organizing%20demonstrations%20hostile%20to%20the%20government%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETwo%20months%20later%20in%20June%201966%2C%20he%20observed%20that%20Indians%20could%20observe%20that%20the%20existence%20of%20Israel%20%E2%80%9Cconstitutes%20a%20wedge%20between%20the%20Arab%20states%20that%20prevents%20the%20establishment%20of%20an%20Arab%20empire%E2%80%9D.%20%E2%80%9CIndia%20is%20not%20interested%20in%20establishing%20such%20an%20empire%2C%20neither%20led%20by%20%5BEgyptian%20President%5D%20Nasser%20nor%20by%20anyone%20else%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20day%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20independence%20anniversary%20on%20August%2015%2C%201966%2C%20the%20head%20of%20the%20Political-Economic%20Planning%20Department%2C%20Ilan%20Aryeh%2C%20suggested%20at%20a%20meeting%20of%20the%20foreign%20ministry%20that%20there%20should%20be%20%E2%80%9Ccautious%20contact%20with%20the%20Jan%20Sangh%20party%20(perhaps%20through%20the%20Mossad)%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDuring%20the%20meeting%2C%20another%20foreign%20ministry%20official%20said%20that%20the%20Israel%20consul%20was%20already%20in%20contact%20with%20the%20Jan%20Sangh%20party%2C%20but%20doubted%20that%20there%20was%20%E2%80%9Cany%20room%20for%20tightening%20ties%20with%20an%20extreme%20nationalist%20party%20that%20has%20no%20chance%20of%20coming%20to%20power%20or%20a%20coalition%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20March%2014%2C%201967%2C%20the%20Israeli%20consul%20wrote%20in%20a%20telegram%20that%20the%20Jan%20Sangh%20had%20included%20a%20demand%20for%20full%20diplomatic%20relations%20with%20Israel%20in%20its%20manifesto.%20Two%20months%20later%2C%20the%20Israeli%20ambassador%20to%20Nepal%2C%20Moshe%20Arel%20reported%20to%20Tel%20Aviv%20on%20May%2022%2C%201967%20that%20he%20had%20met%20with%20a%20Jan%20Sangh%20lawmaker%2C%20M.L.%20Sondhi%2C%20in%20Kathmandu.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20Sondhi%20was%20the%20MP%20from%20New%20Delhi%2C%20he%20said%20that%20%E2%80%9Clocal%20government%20in%20the%20Delhi%20region%20had%20passed%20onto%20the%20hands%20of%20Jan%20Sangh%E2%80%9D.%20Sondhi%20explained%2C%20as%20per%20the%20Israeli%20diplomatic%20telegram%20quoted%20in%20%3Cem%3EHaaretz%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20that%20%E2%80%9CIt%20is%20now%20possible%20to%20put%20the%20Indian%20government%20to%20various%20tests%20in%20the%20Israeli%20context%2C%20the%20result%20of%20which%20will%20be%20the%20undermining%20of%20the%20existing%20anti-Israel%20policy.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20few%20months%20later%20in%20January%201968%2C%20Sondhi%20was%20in%20Phnom%20Penh%2C%20where%20he%20met%20with%20the%20Israeli%20ambassador%20to%20Cambodia%2C%20Raphael%20Ben%20Shalom%2C%20who%20wrote%20that%20the%20Indian%20lawmaker%20told%20him%20that%20he%20was%20ready%20to%20organise%20a%20%E2%80%9Cprotest%20of%20hundreds%20of%20thousands%E2%80%9D%20in%20support%20of%20full%20diplomatic%20ties%20with%20Israel.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20addition%2C%20through%20the%20same%20middleman%2C%20the%20consulate%20%E2%80%9Ccoordinated%20queries%20with%20lawmakers%20from%20Jan%20Sangh%20designed%20to%20criticize%20and%20embarrass%20the%20New%20Delhi%20government%20on%20the%20issue%20of%20its%20abnormal%20relations%20with%20Israel%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20his%20advice%20to%20Israeli%20diplomats%2C%20Sondhi%20also%20reportedly%20suggested%20that%20Israel%20should%20replace%20its%20%E2%80%9Cfixer%20in%20India%20as%20he%20was%20also%20a%20middleman%20for%20Taiwan%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20Israel%20seems%20to%20have%20continued%20with%20the%20same%20middleman%20to%20arrange%20local%20contacts%20for%20several%20years.%20In%201973%2C%20the%20head%20of%20the%20Asia%20department%20in%20the%20Israeli%20foreign%20ministry%20wrote%20to%20the%20consulate%20that%20their%20middleman%20is%20%E2%80%9Cstrongly%20identified%20with%20the%20far%20right%E2%80%9D.%20%E2%80%9CHe%20also%20serves%20as%20a%20middleman%20for%20Taiwan%20and%20is%20very%20active%20in%20all%20kinds%20of%20anti-communist%20organizations%20and%20activities%20that%20smell%20of%20the%20right%20and%20the%20CIA%2C%E2%80%9D%20added%20deputy%20director%20Yaacov%20Shimoni%20in%20his%20telegram.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EHaaretz%3C%2Fem%3E%20wrote%20that%20during%20the%20%E2%80%9970s%2C%20the%20consulate%2C%20through%20the%20same%20middleman%2C%20%E2%80%9Ccoordinated%20queries%20with%20lawmakers%20from%20Jan%20Sangh%20designed%20to%20criticize%20and%20embarrass%20the%20New%20Delhi%20government%20on%20the%20issue%20of%20its%20abnormal%20relations%20with%20Israel%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOver%20a%20decade%20later%2C%20another%20telegram%20from%20the%20Israeli%20consulate%20to%20the%20foreign%20ministry%20on%20October%2030%2C%201985%20refers%20to%20a%20middleman%20who%20organised%20meeting%20with%20the%20far-right%20parties%20%E2%80%9Cwho%20used%20to%20receive%20large%20payments%20from%20us%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBesides%20Jan%20Sangh%2C%20the%20Israeli%20consul%20in%20Mumbai%2C%20Reuven%20Dafni%2C%20also%20kept%20contact%20with%20the%20Shiv%20Sena%20party.%20A%201968%20telegram%20by%20Dafni%2C%20who%20had%20been%20active%20underground%20in%20Hungary%20to%20save%20Jews%20during%20the%20Holocaust%2C%20described%20the%20Shiv%20Sena%20as%20%E2%80%9Cobviously%20demagogic%20fascist%E2%80%9D%20and%20said%20that%20it%20held%20demonstrations%20in%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20style%20of%20the%20Nazis%20in%20the%20%E2%80%9930s%20in%20Germany%20and%20Austria%3A%20breaking%20windows%20of%20mainly%20foreign%20shops%2C%20removing%20foreign%20workers%20from%20various%20workplaces%2C%20etc%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20repeated%20the%20parallels%20in%20another%20telegram%20in%20February%201969%2C%20where%20he%20said%20that%20Bombay%20riots%20was%20instigated%20by%20the%20Shiv%20Sena%2C%20which%20had%20%E2%80%9Cclear%20fascist%20foundations%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDuring%20the%20October%201973%20Yom%20Kippur%2C%20a%20rally%20was%20held%20in%20Bombay%20in%20support%20of%20Israel%20with%20participation%20from%20the%20Shiv%20Sena%20and%20Jan%20Sangh%20%E2%80%9Cin%20coordination%20with%20the%20Israeli%20consulate%E2%80%9D.%20The%20Israeli%20consul%2C%20Joshua%20Trigor%2C%20wrote%20back%20that%20Shiv%20Sena%20chief%20Bal%20Thackeray%20and%20a%20Jan%20Sangh%20MP%20gave%20speeches%20in%20support%20of%20Israel.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EReferring%20to%20a%20meeting%20with%20the%20president%20and%20vice%20president%20of%20Hindu%20Mahasabha%2C%20Trigor%20wrote%20in%20November%201973%20that%20the%20leadership%20gave%20him%20a%20detailed%20report%20on%20how%20they%20had%20made%20pro-Israeli%20speeches%20and%20demonstrations%20during%20the%20Yom%20Kippur%20war.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20Hindu%20Mahasabha%E2%80%99s%20political%20power%20may%20have%20waned%2C%20Trigor%20felt%20that%20%E2%80%9Cit%E2%80%99s%20good%20that%20they%20also%20sympathize%20with%20us%20%E2%80%93%20even%20if%20one%20of%20the%20reasons%20for%20this%20is%20their%20hatred%20of%20Muslims%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEmboldened%20by%20the%20outreach%20to%20the%20Hindu%20Mahasabha%2C%20the%20Israeli%20consulate%20received%20a%20%E2%80%9Csurprise%20guest%E2%80%9D%20%E2%80%93%20Gopal%20Godse%2C%20brother%20of%20Nathuram%20Godse%2C%20the%20murderer%20of%20Mahatma%20Gandhi.%20Gopal%20Godse%20had%20also%20been%20convicted%20with%20a%20life%20sentence%2C%20but%20released%20in%201965.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20his%20report%2C%20Israeli%20diplomat%20Gideon%20Ben%20Ami%20said%20that%20he%20hadn%E2%80%99t%20known%20in%20advance%20of%20Godse%E2%80%99s%20visit%2C%20but%20since%20%E2%80%9Cit%20was%20already%20too%20late%20for%20its%20cancellation%2C%20I%20politely%20listened%20to%20his%20words%E2%80%A6%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGodse%20apparently%20spoke%20%E2%80%9Cpassionately%20about%20his%20hatred%20of%20Muslims%E2%80%9D.%20He%20also%20inquired%20whether%20the%20consulate%20would%20%E2%80%9Clend%20its%20help%20in%20printing%20the%20defense%20speech%20of%20his%20brother%20who%20was%20executed%20%5Bin%201949%5D%20and%20spread%20it%20in%20Israel%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CBen%20Ami%20wrote%20that%20he%20had%20firmly%20rejected%20the%20proposal%20and%20avoided%20entering%20into%20an%20ideological%20polemic%20with%20Gopal%20Godse.%20His%20embarrassment%20was%20due%20to%20the%20fact%20that%20the%20brother%20of%20Gandhi%E2%80%99s%20murderer%20had%20visited%20the%20consulate%2C%20not%20the%20consulate%E2%80%99s%20connection%20with%20the%20far%20right%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20the%20%3Cem%3EHaaretz%3C%2Fem%3E%20article.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20continuing%20saga%20of%20Israeli%20diplomats%20meeting%20with%20the%20Jan%20Sangh%20leadership%20over%20the%20decades%20to%20hear%20about%20their%20sympathy%20for%20Tel%20Aviv%20and%20disapproval%20of%20the%20Union%20government%E2%80%99s%20position%2C%20Israeli%20consul%20Trigor%20wrote%20that%20he%20%E2%80%9Cpersonally%20heard%20this%20from%20party%20president%20LK%20Advani%20at%20our%20meeting%20in%20Delhi%20in%201973%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDuring%20the%20Emergency%20years%2C%20Israeli%20diplomats%20had%20difficulty%20in%20maintaining%20contacts%20with%20the%20Jan%20Sangh%20and%20other%20right-wing%20parties%2C%20as%20their%20leaders%20had%20gone%20underground%20or%20been%20arrested.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20when%20the%20Janta%20coalition%20swept%20to%20power%20in%201977%2C%20the%20Jan%20Sangh%20came%20to%20the%20centre.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20senior%20US%20diplomat%2C%20National%20Security%20Council%E2%80%99s%20Thomas%20Thornton%2C%20informed%20the%20Israeli%20ambassador%20in%20Washington%20David%20Turgeman%20that%20%E2%80%9Cthose%20who%20pursue%20a%20less%20hostile%20line%20to%20Israel%20are%20organized%20within%20the%20framework%20of%20Janata%E2%80%9D.%20Turgeman%20wrote%20in%20his%20telegram%20dated%20March%2025%2C%201977%20that%20Thornton%20told%20him%20that%20the%20%E2%80%9Cright-wing%20Jan%20Sangh%2C%20because%20of%20its%20anti-Muslim%20Hindu%20nature%2C%20is%20a%20supporter%20of%20Israel%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20profile%20of%20Atal%20Bihari%20Vajpayee%2C%20the%20new%20foreign%20minister%20in%20the%20Janta%20government%2C%20mentioned%20that%20he%20had%20once%20led%20a%20demonstration%20against%20the%20PLO%20representatives%20landing%20in%20Mumbai%2C%20which%20led%20to%20their%20plane%20being%20diverted%20to%20Delhi%2C%20an%20internal%20Israeli%20diplomatic%20telegram%20noted%20in%20April%201977.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20per%20another%20telegram%2C%20a%20US%20official%20in%20the%20State%20Department%20also%20explained%20to%20his%20Israeli%20interlocutor%20that%20the%20success%20of%20the%20Jan%20Sangh%20was%20due%20to%20%E2%80%9Cits%20close%20ties%20with%20the%20Hindu%20religious%20militia%20movement%20Rashtriya%20Swayamsevak%20Sangh%E2%80%9D.%20He%20also%20noted%20that%20the%20electoral%20success%20was%20due%20to%20the%20RSS%20doing%20%E2%80%9Cwonders%20in%20recruiting%20voters%20in%20the%20elections%20for%20Janata%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20was%20also%20being%20reported%20back%20by%20Israeli%20diplomats%20from%20India%2C%20with%20consul%20Haim%20Divon%20writing%20in%201979%20that%20the%20Jan%20Sangh%E2%80%99s%20main%20strength%20was%20the%20%E2%80%9Cexemplarily%20organized%20extremist%20Rashtriya%20Swayamsevak%20Sangh%E2%80%9D%2C%20adding%20that%20its%20members%20were%20%E2%80%9Cfascists%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFollowing%20the%20breakout%20of%20communal%20violence%2C%20a%20July%201977%20telegram%20from%20Bombay%20consulate%20noted%20that%20%E2%80%9Csince%20the%20sectarian%20riots%20%E2%80%93%20that%20is%2C%20the%20attacks%20on%20the%20Muslim%20minority%20in%20various%20parts%20of%20northern%20India%20%E2%80%93%20increased%20in%20the%20last%20year%2C%20accusations%20have%20been%20made%20against%20Rashtriya%20Swayamsevak%20Sangh%2C%20against%20its%20Jan%20Sangh%20patron%20and%2C%20indirectly%2C%20against%20Prime%20Minister%20Desai%20for%20not%20demanding%20that%20some%20members%20of%20Janata%20sever%20their%20ties%20with%20the%20group%20and%20for%20not%20coming%20out%20firmly%20against%20them%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20the%20Bharatiya%20Janta%20Party%20was%20formed%20in%20April%201980%2C%20then%20Israeli%20consul%20Haim%20Divon%20wrote%20in%20a%20telegram%20that%20the%20new%20party%20%E2%80%9Cis%20actually%20(despite%20its%20denials)%20Jan%20Sangh%20in%20disguise%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20the%20fall%20of%20the%20Janta%20government%2C%20it%20came%20to%20light%20that%20Israeli%20foreign%20minister%20had%20made%20a%20secret%20visit%20to%20India%20and%20met%20with%20Prime%20Minister%20Moraji%20Desai%20in%201977.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20July%201981%2C%20Israeli%20consul%20Yosef%20Hassin%20reported%20back%20that%20he%20had%20asked%20Ram%20Jethmalani%2C%20lawyer%20and%20then%20vice%20president%20of%20the%20BJP%2C%20to%20write%20an%20internal%20party%20paper%20on%20relations%20with%20Israel.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CHassin%20reported%20that%20Jethmalani%20asked%20if%20he%20could%20prepare%20a%20working%20paper%20and%20arguments%20for%20him%20for%20a%20%E2%80%9Cbalanced%20and%20fair%20position%20toward%20Israel%E2%80%9D%20to%20be%20presented%20at%20the%20party%E2%80%99s%20conference.%20Hassin%20noted%20that%20he%20willingly%20complied%20with%20the%20request.%20Jethmalani%20was%20also%20one%20of%20the%20organizers%20of%20the%20abovementioned%20rally%20in%20support%20of%20Israel%20during%20the%20Yom%20Kippur%20War%2C%20in%20coordination%20with%20the%20consulate%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20article%20stated.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20another%20telegram%2C%20Hassin%20observed%20that%20%E2%80%9Cmost%20of%20the%20supporters%20and%20friends%20of%20Israel%20in%20India%20come%20from%20among%20its%20ranks%20%E2%80%93%20on%20the%20basis%20of%20hatred%20of%20Haman%20more%20than%20love%20of%20Mordechai%E2%80%9D.%20He%20was%20referring%20to%20the%20story%20of%20the%20Book%20of%20Esther%20in%20the%20Hebrew%20Bible%20in%20which%20Haman%2C%20the%20grand%20vizier%20of%20the%20Achaemenid%20King%2C%20plots%20to%20have%20all%20Jews%20in%20Persia%20killed%20after%20Mordecai%2C%20a%20Jewish%20man%2C%20refuses%20to%20prostrate%20before%20him.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20an%20overview%20of%20Israel%E2%80%99s%20relations%20with%20India%2C%20a%20report%20written%20by%20the%20Isreali%20foreign%20ministry%E2%80%99s%20Asia%20department%20in%20June%201982%20observed%20that%20the%20%E2%80%9Cfactors%20working%20in%20our%20favour%E2%80%9D%20included%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20existence%20of%20the%20Hindu-Muslim%20conflict%2C%20which%20was%20a%20deep%20and%20sharp%20rift%2C%20and%20the%20formation%20of%20the%20anti-Muslim%20right-wing%20Bharatiya%20Janata%20Party%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20same%20month%2C%20Hassin%20was%20forced%20to%20leave%20the%20country%20after%20the%20Indian%20government%20declared%20him%20%3Cem%3Epersona%20non%20grata%3C%2Fem%3E%20after%20he%20attacked%20the%20Indian%20government%20for%20its%20pro-Arab%20policy%20in%20a%20news%20interview.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1710125836000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2019%2F11%2F27192051%2F20191018093103.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcommunalism%2Fisraeli-diplomats-forged-deep-ties-with-hindu-right-wing-from-early-60s-documents-reveal%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Diplomatic%20telegrams%20show%20that%20while%20Israeli%20diplomats%20explicitly%20referred%20to%20the%20far-right%20membe