0back%20then%2C%20nobody%20in%20India%20was%20manufacturing%20it%20on%20a%20significant%20scale.%20But%20they%20eventually%20found%20a%20company%20in%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F329424%2Fludhiana-woman-grows-200-plants-in-terrace-garden-watch-video%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ELudhiana%2C%20Punjab%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20was%20importing%20batteries%20and%20distributing%20them%20all%20over%20the%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CAs%20students%2C%20we%20approached%20that%20company%20for%20a%20battery%20and%20they%20even%20agreed%20to%20give%20us%20one%20for%20this%20project.%20But%20for%20six%20months%20they%20kept%20delaying%20the%20delivery%20of%20this%20battery%2C%20and%20eventually%2C%20we%20couldn%E2%80%99t%20participate%20in%20the%20competition.%20Frustrated%20by%20this%20outcome%2C%20Vikrant%20and%20I%20began%20discussing%20why%20these%20Li-ion%20batteries%20aren%E2%80%99t%20being%20made%20in%20India%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20recalls.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20realised%20that%20in%20these%20batteries%20you%20have%20Li-ion%20cells%20and%20these%20aren%E2%80%99t%20manufactured%20in%20India%20for%20the%20very%20simple%20reason%20that%20you%20can%E2%80%99t%20find%20the%20raw%20materials%2C%20i.e.%20lithium%2C%20cobalt%20and%20nickel%2C%20required%20to%20make%20them.%20Also%2C%20at%20the%20time%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F300789%2Fretrofitting-how-to-convert-your-old-cars-into-electric-vehicles%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eelectric%20vehicle%3C%2Fa%3E%20(EV)%20consumption%20wasn%E2%80%99t%20too%20heavy%20and%20no%20one%20realised%20that%20this%20sector%20would%20take%20off%20soon.%20At%20the%20time%2C%20whatever%20OEMs%20(original%20equipment%20manufacturers)%20in%20India%20needed%2C%20they%20were%20importing%20those%20materials%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20part%20of%20their%20college%20semester%20project%2C%20they%20decided%20to%20build%20Li-ion%20cells%20at%20a%20Rs%20200%20crore%20R%26amp%3BD%20laboratory%20set%20up%20on%20campus.%20%E2%80%9CWe%20ordered%20lithium%20and%20cobalt%20from%20China.%20Due%20to%20various%20reasons%2C%20these%20materials%20didn%E2%80%99t%20arrive%20on%20time%20for%20our%20project.%20To%20complete%20it%2C%20we%20bought%20some%20old%20Li-ion%20cells%20from%20the%20market%2C%20extracted%20whatever%20materials%20we%20could%20in%20very%20impure%20forms%20and%20then%20fabricated%20Li-ion%20cells%20(half%20cells)%20that%20delivered%20some%20energy%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20recalls.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CTo%20acquire%20these%20materials%20in%20India%2C%20we%20needed%20to%20start%20recycling%20old%20Li-ion%20batteries.%20We%20predicted%20that%20a%20lot%20of%20Li-ion%20batteries%20are%20going%20to%20enter%20the%20country%2C%20and%20if%20we%20recycle%20them%2C%20these%20materials%20can%20be%20reused%20to%20make%20cells.%20See%2C%20you%20can%20recycle%20metals%20like%20lithium%20infinitely.%20That%E2%80%99s%20how%20the%20idea%20of%20BatX%20Energies%20was%20born.%20We%20spent%20the%20following%20semesters%20researching%20what%E2%80%99s%20required%20to%20recycle%20Li-ion%20batteries%20on%20a%20larger%20scale%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20502px)%20100vw%2C%20502px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2FBatX-Founders-1709299079.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22502%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Gurugram%20Startup%20is%20recycling%20Lithium-ion%20batteries%20%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2FBatX-Founders-1709299079.jpg%20502w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2FBatX-Founders-1709299079-198x300.jpg%20198w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2FBatX-Founders-1709299079-500x757.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2FBatX-Founders-1709299079-150x227.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-343651%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22760%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EUtkarsh%20Singh%20and%20Vikrant%20Singh%20got%20into%20the%20business%20of%20recycling%20Lithium-ion%20batteries%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20college%2C%20Vikrant%20and%20Utkarsh%20were%20very%20clear%20about%20learning%20what%20it%20takes%20to%20run%20a%20company%20before%20starting%20one.%20They%20worked%20for%20a%20little%20over%20one%20year%20in%20different%20companies%20with%20Vikrant%20engaged%20in%20R%26amp%3BD%20work%20while%20Utkarsh%20dealt%20with%20the%20management%20side%20of%20things.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAmid%20the%20pandemic%20in%20July%202020%2C%20they%20got%20back%20together%20and%20established%20BatX%20Energies%2C%20which%20is%20today%20a%20major%20Lithium-ion%20battery%20recycling%20startup%20which%20produces%20battery-grade%20materials.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20their%20core%20objectives%20is%20to%20create%20a%20domestic%20circular%20supply%20chain%20of%20materials%20like%20lithium%2C%20nickel%20and%20cobalt%2C%20among%20others%2C%20and%20lessen%20the%20requirement%20for%20mining%20them.%20The%20company%20extracts%20rare%20earth%20metals%2C%20such%20as%20lithium%2C%20cobalt%2C%20nickel%20and%20manganese%20from%20used%20Li-ion%20cells%2C%20which%20are%20then%20bought%20by%20a%20variety%20of%20industries%20%E2%80%94%20including%20EVs%2C%20pharmaceuticals%2C%20electroplating%20and%20fertiliser.%20But%20if%20these%20used%20cells%20have%20some%20charge%20left%2C%20they%20repurpose%20them%20into%20batteries%20for%20off-grid%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F256764%2Fmumbai-startup-electric-vehicle-features-charger-cost-install-magenta-street-light-ev-charging-solutions-s